<p>The <code>bool</code> tag defines a boolean condition.</p>

<h2>Basic Boolean (True)</h2>
<pre>{open}bool 'isActive'{close}1{open}/bool{close}

{open}isActive{close}
  Active!
{open}else{close}
  Inactive
{open}/isActive{close}</pre>
{bool 'isActive'}1{/bool}
{isActive}
<p style="color:green">Active!</p>
{else}
<p>Inactive</p>
{/isActive}

<h2>Boolean (False)</h2>
<pre>{open}bool 'isHidden'{close}0{open}/bool{close}

{open}isHidden{close}
  This won't show
{open}else{close}
  isHidden is false
{open}/isHidden{close}</pre>
{bool 'isHidden'}0{/bool}
{isHidden}
<p>This won't show</p>
{else}
<p style="color:red">isHidden is false, so else shows</p>
{/isHidden}

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>The bool tag creates a named condition that can be used as a tag with {open}else{close} support.</p>
